{
  "text": "on the other hand, several authors [CITATION_1] reported that the right DLPFC, but not the left, contributes to the encoding of visual-object associations [CITATION_2] and the left but not the right DLPFC plays a crucial role in the encoding of verbal material [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , supporting the theories of material specificity.",
